The paper discusses techniques for interpreting and ranking responses to free-format queries on unstructured text, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which are also relevant to NLP. The paper also uses probabilistic language models and discriminative learning, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (ML) and statistical modeling, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with structured knowledge bases and entity search, which are topics related to databases (DB), indicating that cs.DB is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
